HEADWORD: Conservatoire
<hw>Con`ser"va*toire`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A public place of instruction in any special
branch, esp. music and the arts. [See <er>Conservatory</er>,
3].</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

